title: Energy levels in F-18 from alpha particle reactions in nitrogen.

x4freetext: A beam of singly charged helium ions collimated to a
circular area of 1 mm diameter entered a scattering
chamber through a differential pumping system.
A movable proportional counter filled with
nitrogen to 7 cm Hg subtended an angle of about two
degrees at the scattering volume and was accurately at
angles up to 147.5 degr. in the laboratory. A very thin
window of Formvar some 6-8 mu-g/cm2 thick allowed us
to efficiently detect alpha particles down to about
40 keV.
Gas target was used.  The scattering gas pressure
was kept around 3 mm Hg. The effective target thickness
was of the order of 400 eV and was therefore completely
negligible.

x4freetext: Because of the low relative yield of protons it turned
out to be necessary to interpose an appropriate
thickness of nickel absorber foil in front of the
proportional counter in order to stop all alpha
particles and permit protons to be detected. Also, the
solid angle subtended by the counter was increased by a
factor of 20. A thickness of 0.00015 in. Ni foil
allowed us to observe protons at angles greater
than 90 degr. (lab).
